4476ac825 ("Raise gcc version<br />requirement to 4.9"):<br /><br />   "In particular, raising the minimum to 4.9 means that we can now just<br />    assume _Generic() exists, which is likely the much better replacement<br />    for a lot of very convoluted built-time magic with conditionals on<br />    sizeof and/or __builtin_choose_expr() with same_type() etc"<br /><br />but we haven't used it much since.<br /><br />The "seqprop" code for picking the right lock for seqlock is perhaps<br />the main example, and staring at that code will make you go blind, so<br />look away.<br /><br />            Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
